# Session 19 Handover — Fumage

## What was done this session

### No Fumage code changes

This session contained no edits to the Fumage codebase, routes, database, or guide articles.

### External research deliverable: clone fragrance brand spreadsheet

Produced a standalone CSV at `/Users/scottreisinger/clone_fragrance_brands.csv` — not part of the Fumage repo.

**Contents:** Top 50 global clone/dupe/inspired-by fragrance companies, ranked 1–50, focused on masculine and unisex fragrances. Each brand has 10 fragrance rows.

**Columns:** Brand · Website · Rank · Fragrance Name · Inspired By / Dupe Target · Gender Label · Notes · Popularity Signal · Review Signal

**Total:** 501 lines (1 header + 500 data rows).

**Methodology:** Web research across Fragrantica, Basenotes, Reddit r/fragrance, brand sites, and review aggregators. Three research agents contributed data across successive passes. Sub-label duplicates (e.g. "Armaf (extended picks)", "Lattafa Oud Mood") were collapsed into parent brands; the freed slots were filled with independent houses.

**Known data quality flags:**
- Benchmark Fragrances / Lathe Parfums — minimal online presence; all rows data-limited.
- Rave Scents — Lattafa sub-brand (kept by explicit user decision); rows 6–10 data-limited.
- Lootah Perfumes — traditional Emirati house; most dupe targets listed as "Original composition."
- Pendora Scents and Asdaaf — sub-brands of Paris Corner and Lattafa respectively (kept by explicit user decision).

